# Token Efficiency Principles

1. Never re-read a file you already have in context. If Edit/Write succeeded, the change is applied.
2. Avoid unnecessary tool calls. Read files directly when you know the path.
3. Run independent tool calls in parallel, not sequentially.
4. Delegate outputs longer than 20 lines to subagents.
5. **Never repeat information the user already provided** (most important).
6. Use session-injected state (git status, branch, recent commits) before re-querying. Only re-query if state changed mid-session.
7. Run validation **once after all code changes are done**. Order: lint > build > check > test (stop on first failure).
